    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Chop your <strong>leek[s]</strong> in half lengthways, wash thoroughly to remove any grit then top, tail and slice finely</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop your<strong> cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-king-prawn-crab-and-chilli-stracci/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a little drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced leek </strong>and a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until softened</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-king-prawn-crab-and-chilli-stracci/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the leek is cooking, zest your<strong> lemon[s]</strong> (try to grate lightly with a micro-plane or sharp box grater and avoid grating the white pith, as this is very bitter), then cut in half</p><p>Peel <strong>half</strong> your<strong> Italian hard cheese </strong>until you end up with a pile of cheese shavings and grate the rest</p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-king-prawn-crab-and-chilli-stracci/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the leek has softened, add the<strong> halved tomatoes </strong>to the pan with the<strong> chopped garlic</strong>, your <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Cook for 5-6 min or until the tomatoes have softened</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-king-prawn-crab-and-chilli-stracci/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Break your <strong>lasagne sheets </strong>into medium-sized pieces \u2013 these are your <strong>pasta stracci</strong></p><p>Heat a large pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> over a high heat with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>pasta stracci</strong> to the boiling water, stirring to separate the pasta pieces</p><p>Cook for 7-9 min, stirring from time to time to prevent the pasta from sticking, then drain the <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>pasta stracci</strong>,<strong> </strong>reserving a little <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-king-prawn-crab-and-chilli-stracci/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Increase the heat to medium-high, then drain and add your <strong>king prawns</strong> to the pan with the tomatoes and cook for 4-5 min or until the prawns are cooked through</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-king-prawn-crab-and-chilli-stracci/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the prawns are cooked through, add your <strong>crab meat</strong>, <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong>, <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong> (you'll use the shavings later!), <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>pasta stracci</strong> and a splash of <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p><p>Cook for 1 min, then remove from the heat and stir through your <strong>soft cheese</strong>,<strong> </strong>most of the <strong>lemon zest</strong>, a squeeze of <strong>lemon juice </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>pepper </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>creamy king prawn, crab & chilli stracci</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-king-prawn-crab-and-chilli-stracci/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut the<strong> remaining lemon </strong>into 1 wedge per person</p><p>Serve the <strong>creamy king prawn, crab & chilli stracci</strong> topped with the <strong>remaining lemon zest </strong>and the<strong> Italian hard cheese shavings</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>salad </strong>to the side, then drizzle with <strong>olive oil</strong> and garnish with a <strong>lemon wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
